text: The goldcrest is a passerine bird in the kinglet family. Goldcrest may also refer to: * USS Goldcrest (AM-78), a minesweeper commissioned in 1940 * USS Goldcrest (AM-80), a steel merchant trawler built in 1928 * USS Goldcrest (AMCU-24), a minesweeper laid down in 1944 * Goldcrest Films, a British film production company * Goldcrest Point, a point of Bird Island, South Georgia * Goldcrest, a cultivar of Cupressus macrocarpa ==See also== * USS Goldcrest, a list of US warships
title: Goldcrest (disambiguation)
